      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>One of two inscribed medeallions in an elaborate tesselated pavement. Tesserae are white, gray, black, yellow, green and two shades of red, 65 tessera to 100 cm². Dimesniosn given are just the diameter of the medallion. The entire pavement is 6.80 wide and 7.20 long. The medallion has an elaborate border 0.20 wide of white vines on a black field. At the begnning and end are crosses; above and below are branches with pomegranates. The nomina sacra are abbreviated by suspension and marked with bars.</p>
         </div>
